The paper deals with organizing large databases of imagery and geometry using unsupervised learning and interactive ranking. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of label propagation and active suggestion of data points also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with organizing databases, which suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB).
